# Definition of Done

A feature is **COMPLETE** only when **every** item below is satisfied. Otherwise, do **not** say "the feature is complete."

## Checklist

```text
✓ Requirements understood and acceptance criteria met
✓ Architecture approved (review gates passed)
✓ Database reviewed (if schema changes)
✓ API documented and contract followed (if API work)
✓ Backend complete (if applicable)
✓ Frontend complete with all UI states (if applicable)
✓ Unit tests pass
✓ Integration tests pass
✓ E2E tests pass (if user-facing flow)
✓ Security reviewed (security-engineer)
✓ Performance reviewed (performance-reviewer, if API/hot path)
✓ Refactor applied (if review required changes)
✓ Documentation updated (docs/ + Docs/ as applicable)
✓ ADR written (if architectural decision)
✓ Code reviewed (code-reviewer)
✓ Build passes
✓ Lint passes
✓ Type check passes
✓ Notion task set to Done
✓ Ready for production
```

## Verification order

```text
Build → Lint → Types → Unit → Integration → E2E
→ Performance → Security → Code review → DoD → Notion Done
```

## Code review dimensions

Architecture · Naming · Performance · Security · Testing · Readability · Maintainability · Scalability

Improve implementation based on findings before marking complete.
